    "This entails keeping up with current scientific literature and clinical recommendations to assure relevancy and accuracy in answering orthopedic exam questions.",
    "In addition, integrating generative AI with large databases of medical imagery and diagnostic tools could boost its capacity to effectively analyze complex clinical scenarios.",
    "Enhanced algorithms could also offer personalized learning experiences, adapting to the unique needs of each student and providing tailored educational content.",
    "Moreover, improved AI-human interaction capabilities could simulate realistic patient scenarios, enhancing practical skills training.",
    "Emphasizing these characteristics, as well as enhancing the cognitive abilities of generative AI, will be critical in fully leveraging its potential to complement orthopedic education and practice.To effectively integrate generative AI into the orthopedic curriculum, a structured, phased approach is recommended that aligns with educational goals and ethical standards, equipping students with both foundational knowledge and practical skills."
